.TH FREE 1 "2026-01-15" "free-macos 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
free \- Linux-like memory summary for macOS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B free
[\-h]
[\-b|\-k|\-m|\-g]
[\-w]
[\-t]
[\-s \fISECONDS\fR]
[\-c \fICOUNT\fR]
[\-\-details]
[\-\-version]
[\-\-help]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B free
prints a summary of memory and swap usage on macOS in a format similar to GNU
.BR free (1)
on Linux.
.PP
The output is an approximation based on macOS memory accounting. Values may differ
from Linux
.BR free (1)
because macOS classifies and manages memory differently.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Human-readable output (default).
.TP
.B \-b
Show output in bytes.
.TP
.B \-k
Show output in kibibytes.
.TP
.B \-m
Show output in mebibytes.
.TP
.B \-g
Show output in gibibytes.
.TP
.B \-w
Wide output (accepted for GNU free compatibility).
.TP
.B \-t
Display a line with totals (Mem + Swap).
.TP
.BI "\-s " SECONDS
Repeat printing every
.I SECONDS
seconds.
.TP
.BI "\-c " COUNT
Repeat count with
.BR \-s .
A value of 0 means repeat forever.
.TP
.B \-\-details
Print an additional macOS-specific breakdown line (wired, compressed, active, inactive, etc.).
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.SH OUTPUT
The main table contains:
.TP
.B total
Total physical memory (or swap).
.TP
.B used
Approximate used memory excluding reclaimable cache.
.TP
.B fr
